        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 1:20PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 120 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bogata, or 9 miles north of Hagansport, moving north at 60 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Detroit, Clarksville, Idabel, Winfield, Pittsburg, Woodland, Redland,
Miller's Cove, Hagansport, Rocky Mound, Harvard, Kanawha, Mount
Vernon, Boxelder, Garvin, Bogata, Kiomatia, Johntown, Farmers Hill,
and Mount Pleasant.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 PM CDT for
northeastern Texas.</instruction>
